        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24591/10–2545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-25T19:00:00-05:00">October 25, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>601. Although Russian withdrawal from Tehran was advertised, it has not actually
                    taken place, British have informed American Military Attaché London. Emb’s
                    comments on this statement would be appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
